  "unmapped_findings": [
    "Addition of Al up to ~10 wt% leads to density reduction of up to 8% and formation of ferrite (BCC) phase.",
    "Young's modulus reduction upon Al addition was reported by Rana et al., limiting automotive use, but is not measured in this study.",
    "Yield ratio (YS/UTS) calculated: 98%CR not available, 5 min anneal 0.85, 60 min anneal 0.67.",
    "Strain hardening rate curves (Fig. 8b) shown for 5 and 60 min annealed samples; higher rate for 60 min.",
    "The ordered phase identified as Fe3Al with D03 structure; a possible B2 (FeAl) phase was indicated by low-intensity peak at ~23 T in Mössbauer spectra for Al ≥ 6.8%, but volume fraction low.",
    "Lattice frictional stress for Fe-Al at room temperature taken as 41 MPa from literature for 0.4 wt% C steel due to unavailability of data.",
    "Comparison with dual-phase Fe-Mn-Al-C low-density steels: the single-phase Fe-6.8Al after 5 min anneal (YS=700 MPa, elongation 20%) rivals properties of lean alloyed duplex steels (YS=472 MPa, UTS=635 MPa, elongation 19.7% from Rana et al. [8,9]).",
    "Shear bands observed at ~40° to RD in 98% CR sample; these indicate non-uniform deformation.",
    "98% CR sample did not show measurable UTS because failure occurred soon after yielding.",
    "SAXS intensity at high q (>3 nm^-1) showed incoherent flat background; at low q (<0.3 nm^-1) intensity decays as q^-4, attributed to larger heterogeneities (grains/grain boundaries)."
  ]
